comment:
You *KNOW* that if AH was confirmed in the film... she would be shouting it from the rooftops, and posting pictures constantly!  Posting all these old pictures from "Aquaman" and "Justice League" is strange.  Some of the large sets are built in the UK, and some are built in Australia, and of course, the beautiful beaches that they film on are located in Australia's Gold Coast, but they filmed in Italy as well.  AH should be worried that Australia *WILL* grant her visa, and then will arrest her when she is filming there.  There is a far more critical concern for her, and that is cast insurance.  Robert Downey Jr. was no longer insurable after his problems with substances and the law, and Mel Gibson literally stepped in and personally covered the insurance for "The Singing Detective", which turned RDJ's career around.  Lindsey Lohan is uninsurable. Cast insurance will be exceptionally expensive for AH, as she is in the middle of serious ongoing litigation, *AND* is under felony investigation in two countries... *IF* she can even *BE* insured.  She could be months into shooting when criminal charges could brought against her, or the subornation of perjury/perjury charges could be levied by Australia or the United States... which would mean that "Aquaman 2" would have to go to the expense of reshooting her role -- and would have to deal with the bad publicity.  That's only *SOME* of the many things a studio has to take into account when considering AH.  

There is no denying that AH has been out of the information loop for at least a year.  In 2020, Mr. Depp's team made direct reference in court documents to the "Aquaman 2" shoot beginning in June, while AH's team were still stating the film would begin shooting in the Spring.  AH would *HAVE* to be in serious training right now, but even her last Tweet with the picture of Jason Momoa isn't current.  He's promoting "See" right now, and is sporting a much longer beard than he has in the picture with AH.  Something's up!  If things are looking unfavorable, even Elon Musk stepping up to pay her insurance wouldn't secure her the role.  She may be too much of a liability for the studio.  We can hope!
